Arkansas Department of Education
September 11 at 7:50 AM ¬∑

September 11, 2001, is a day that our nation will never forget. Let us all take a few moments to remember the nearly 3,000 people lost that day, their families, and the first responders to each incident.

Traumatic events such as this can have long-lasting impacts on our students and open communication is key. For tips on talking to students after traumatic events, visit http://bit.ly/2m6fAPf. #EngagementMattersAR #ARStudentFocused #NeverForget

Alma Intermediate School Counselor's Corner
September 8 at 6:40 PM ¬∑

üó£ ATTENTION PARENTS!!! ‚ÄºÔ∏è

Alma Intermediate School students now have access to Mrs. Wagner's Virtual School Counseling Office! This is accessible for face to face, remote and blended students through Google Classroom.

This virtual office is full of all kinds of resources for students and parents! I encourage you to explore my virtual office along with your child so you know what is available. YOU can even send in a request for your child to meet with the school counselor, if needed.

Here is a glimpse of what you can find in it...
-Teacher/Parent Google Form for Counselor Request
-Student Check-In Form
-Virtual Calm Down Corner
-Coping skills
-Calming music
-SEL educational videos
-Brain break games
-Virtual SEL library (250+ books!) (Currently having technical issues, so books may not be available at the moment.)
-LOTS of resources for parents!
-PLUS more!

If you have questions about how to access this, please let me know or you might check with your child's teacher.

ALMA YOUTH SOCCER FALL 2020 SEASON REGISTRATION
DEADLINE SEPTEMBER 12, 2020

Online registration for the Fall 2020 season of Alma Youth Soccer is now available for grades Pre K - 8th Grade.

We will ONLY use online registration. If you elected to roll over your player fee from last spring you MUST STILL complete this registration form.

You must complete a form for each player you register. Players do not have to reside in the Alma School District to sign-up.
The fee to play is $20. These dues can be mailed in or paid at evaluations.

Our Evaluation date is still to be determined.

If you are mailing in the dues, please make all checks payable to Alma Athletics - Alma Youth Soccer and mail them to:

Alma Youth Soccer
c/o Coach Sturdivant
Alma Middle School
PO BOX 2229
Alma, AR 72921

More information is provided on the registration form.

post_text:
2020 ‚Äì 2021 SCHOOL YEAR UPDATE

After seeking guidance from medical professionals and learning the opinions of our teachers and school board, Alma School District is implementing a policy for the 2020-2021 school year requiring face coverings for all K-12 students and staff. Almost all school districts in our area are doing the same.

Face coverings will be required when social distancing cannot be achieved. Accommodations will be made for students and staff who are unable to wear face coverings due to health-related or other concerns. Students will be given opportunities throughout the day to remove their face coverings for meals and snacks, as well as during times when physical distancing can be achieved. Students are encouraged to bring their own face coverings each day, but the District will have additional face coverings available for students when needed.

ASD‚Äôs highest priority is the health and well-being of our students and staff and we greatly appreciate everyone‚Äôs cooperation in this matter.

Kacie Stabler
May 26 at 4:37 PM ¬∑

Thursday night it was made official that I will be teaching and coaching at Pottsville! (YAY!!!! ü§óü§óü§ó) We have prayed for me to get closer to home and now it has been answered! I am so excited for what the future holds but I will say I am going to miss my Airedale family. In my time at Alma I have come to know some pretty incredible people.
